description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Synchronicity Care Limited (SCL) /CDD Services are a wholly owned subsidiary company of County Durham and Darlington NHS Foundation Trust (CDDFT). SCL/CDD Services provides a range of non-clinical Estates, Facilities and Procurement services to CDDFT.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;SCL/CDD Services are looking to recruit a hardworking, flexible, enthusiastic and customer focussed individual to join our Domestic Services Team at Darlington Memorial Hospital. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Domestic Assistants are important members of the team who assist with maintaining a clean and welcoming environment over a 24/7 period for patients, staff and visitors within a busy acute hospital.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Successful post holders will be required to carry out specific cleaning and other related duties to set procedures and standards and required to work as part of a team and have the ability to use a degree of initiative to prioritise and organise the daily duties, whilst maintaining a professional approach at all times regardless of the situation. Post holders will be also be expected to be flexible to the needs of the service.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful applicant should preferably have previous cleaning experience in a healthcare environment however full training will be provided and all successful post holders will be expected to work towards gaining a NVQ Level 2 Certificate in Cleaning and Support Services &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;All posts will be subject to a 6 month probation period &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;For this advertised role successful post holders will be expected to work shifts including evening and weekends, full rota will be discussed at interview &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;SCL offers its own Terms and Conditions of employment which differ to the national NHS Terms and Conditions. As an employee in the company you will benefit from:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;• A Competitive salary&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;• Excellent Performance Related Bonus Scheme&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;• Up to 27 days annual leave plus bank holidays (dependant on service and contracted hours)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;• Access to a pension scheme - National Employment Savings Trust (NEST) – CDD Services will pay a 3% contribution (this is over and above the minimum contribution rate at the present time)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;• Night Shift Working Allowances (where appropriate)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;• Bank Holiday Working Allowances (where appropriate)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
